inn1.comm: drops the loosener short outside off and he helps himself to an upper cut to third man
hits a good length on the offstump and he pats it away, Shoaib is ambling in - not at full throttle yet
lands it outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching the keeper
pushes it softly to mid-on
too wide outside off and enough width for him to free his arms, get his front foot forward and bisect the gap between cover and point
holds the length back and keeps the ball outside off, he safely shoulders arms
he overpitches outside off but gets away with it as Watson pushes it hard straight to short mid-off
shortish outside off and a risky shot as he slashes it in the air down the vacant gully position
punched down to the right of mid-off and the fielder does really well to slide and cut it off, good commitment
induces the false shot! He prods forward and the ball kicks up a bit off a good length and goes through straight, very close to th edge
clips it with the angle towards short square leg and there's hesitation but the batsmen stay put
gets across on the backfoot and defends with a dead bat
he gifts him a half volley on the pads and Haddin turns the face of the bat and whips it wide of midwicket, the ball slows down before reaching the rope
strays on the pads again and he clips it with the angle to fine leg
delivers from slightly wide of the crease, the batsman taps it towards short mid-on with soft hands and sets off quickly
the first bit of action for the day, Shoaib drops it short and has Watson fending, Shoaib had something to say to him and Watson returned the pleasantries
drops it short and he fends it to the off side and they take a single
angles it in towards middle and leg and he tucks it to midwicket
Umar Gul bowls a jaffa outside off, he's getting the ball to kick up alarmingly, that was mighty close to that outside edge
gets a half stride forward and defends with soft hands
he prods forward and hangs his bat out but plays with very soft hands, the edge drops well short of Misbah at first slip
chance! Watson swivels and fails to time his pull, the ball travels off the top edge of the bat but drops behind square leg, two fielders chase it
outside off, he moves across and defends on the backfoot
gets across and defends a good length ball on the front foot
that's a poor delivery, really wide outside the leg stump and Akmal has an early workout
slower ball but he picks it early, opens the face of the bat and steers it wide of second slip
slower ball, he gets forward and drops it to the on side
shuffles and clips it to the on side
keeps it on the offstump and he gets forward and defends
gives him width and Haddin gets forward and thumps it hard at the gap between mid-off and cover, the bat speed was tremendous and the ball just sped away
gets across and defends to the off side
rare bad delivery from Gul, he strays on the pads and Watson clips it slightly in the air but bisects the gap between square leg and midwicket, safe shot in the end
that was worth driving miles to see! Gul pitches it up and it's a forward defensive scoop which sends it over wide long-off, excellent timing and a really good follow through
gets behind the line and defends
drops it short and he goes for the pull and places it to fine leg, the fielder is more towards long leg
short again and he works it away down to fine leg again
slower ball and he clips it towards midwicket and the fielder doesn't time his dive well, he palms it to the deep
slower ball and he taps it to mid-on
false shot by Haddin as he swats one from outside off and nearly chips it on the full to mid-on who's up close
gets beside the line and steers it down to backward point
slower ball and he nearly clips it on the full to short fine leg, nice field placing by Younis
cranks up the pace and drops it a bit short, Haddin knocks it to cover and thinks of a single but watson isn't interested
keeps it on a good length and he steers it to cover point
loosener outside the offstump and he opens the face of the bat and steers it to third man
Haddin's in imperious touch, he stays at the crease and chips him high over midwicket, he times it well and the follow through is sound, looked like he played it in his sleep
gets behind the line and pushes it down the track
shuffles and tries to work it round the corner but the ball clips his body and rolls away

lazy elegance from Haddin again, Arafat drops it short of a length and the ball sits up nicely for Haddin to thump it in the air past the bowler and wide of mid-on, he just stayed at the crease and played the shot
bowls it too full and he whips it with the angle wide of midwicket, poor over from Arafat
opens the face of the bat to a slower ball and dabs it to third man
another slower ball and the batsman gets behind and defends with a dead bat
he's seeing it like a football! Shoaib drops it short outside off and it's suicidal on this pitch, Haddin swivels and biffs it wide of short midwicket
shuffles across and clips it with the angle down to deep square leg

Sharp catch by the captain! Haddin makes room to a full ball and tries to scoop it over mid-off, the ball makes contact with the bottom half of the bat and travels quickly to Younis at short mid-off who leaps and takes the catch over his head
gets right across his stumps and defends firmly to mid-off
shuffles and works it to the on side
defends with soft hands and the ball bounces off the pitch and nearly lands on top of the stumps
shuffle and works it with the angle to the on side

looked like a mid-hit at first but the ball was well clear of any fielder, he swings a tad early and the ball swirls in the air for a long while before dropping just short of the rope at deep midwicket
gets across and defends with a half prod forward
he oversteps, Watson mistimes the pull to Afridi at midwicket
Free Hit: It's a friendly half volley on middle and leg and he stays at the crease and lofts through the line and clears the rope at long-on
starts off with the regulation offspinner, North defends
moves across his stumps early and he clips the doosra to short square leg
flighted outside off and defended to the off side
flighted across the left hander and he shuffles and works it wide of square leg
shuffles and clips it to the leg side but fails to clear midwicket
the top spinner, he gets behind and defends
flighted on middle and off and he gets forward and clips it wide of mid-on
loops it into the right hander and Watson drives on the up to mid-off
doesn't quite cover the line and he gets a leading edge to the off side
stays on the backfoot and defends back to the bowler
offers the full face of the bat and pushes it to mid-off
gets behind the line and defends to the off side
gets forward early  and pushes it towards mid-off and takes the single
drops it short and it's an invitation for Watson as he waits for it to turn in, he pulls and places it wide of fine leg who's fielding very square
gets behind the line and defends
gets behind the line and defends
gets a half prod forward and defends down the track
lunges forward and pushes a full delivery to mid-off
flighted on middle and leg and he defends
slower through the air and he gets forward and clips it just wide of square leg and sets off for a quick single
this one comes on straight and he gets forward and steers it to the off side
quicker delivery and North clips it wide of mid-on, deep midwicket runs across and cuts it off
full outside off and pushed firmly to mid-off
slow through the air and he shuffles and drills it to short fine leg
moves across and clips it with the turn to the on side
commits to the front foot and smothers the spin
gets on his knee and sweeps him firmly to fine leg
the doosra, he shapes to drive and gets an inside edge onto his boot

beaten in flight! North chips down the track on seeing the extra flight but Ajmal cleverly gets it to go through straight and foxes him, Akmal effects an easy stumping. North was probably expecting it to turn away. Ajmal set it up the previous ball by bowling the doosra
full outside off and he gets well forward and defends
slower through the air and he lunges forward and smothers the spin
full on middle and off and pushed back to the bowler
tosses it up and bowls it straight, Clarke defends on the front foot again
quicker through the  air and Clarke commits forward early and defends
slower through the air and Clarke gets a thin outside edge which beats slip, gully runs backward and cuts it off
gets across his stumps and pushes it just wide of the diving Ajmal, easy single to long-on
slow through the air and he works it straight to short square-leg
gives it more flight and he chips down the track and pushes it to long-on
works it through the gap between midwicket and square leg
quicker, he clips it straight to midwicket
drops it short and he swivels and swats it along the turf to deep square-leg
short and slightly wide outside off and he rocks back and slams it past the covers, malik pulls it back before the rope
punches it in front of mid-on and sets off for a quick single
tosses it up outside off and he watchfully shoulders arms
quicker through the air and he defends with a dead bat
he bowls the indrifter, he pushes it through the line to mid-on
drops this one short and he gets ready to pull but ends up chopping it to the on side
turns it to short square leg and the non striker tells him to stay back
gets right across his stumps and defends with a dead bat

chance! Ajmal gets it to turn inwards and the ball kicks up a bit too, Clarke is caught unawares and gets a thick outside edge which beats Afirdi at slip, Afridi made the mistake of moving to his right when he should have moved the other way
pushed down the pitch
comes down and pushes it back to the bowler
pulls it to deep square leg and the fielder fumbles
gets forward and defends
gets across his stumps and gets a leading edge to the off side
rocks on the backfoot and cuts wide of point
drops it short and he pulls hard but Younis is alert at midwicket
full outside off and pushed to the off side
flighted on middle and leg, he shuffles and clips it to the on side
rocks back and punches it to cover and sets off
quicker through the air and defended to the offside
shuffles and nudges him softly towards short fine leg
pushes it in front of mid-on and sets off very quickly
bowls it much quicker and he clips it on the full to midwicket
chips down the track and pads it away, Afridi does well to drop it short and keep him quiet
gets well forward and defends to the off side, very close to the pads and Bowden shakes his head
gives it a lot of air, he lunges forward and defends
full outside off and pushed wide of point
dropped it short on the offstump, Watson picked it early and deposited it over midwicket
gets forward to defend and he gets a leading edge which rolls towards mid-off
starts off with a loosener, he rocks back and cuts to sweeper cover
chips down the track and pushes a full delivery to long-off
no turn off the pitch, he defends on the front foot
angles it into the right hander and he clips it away wide of square leg
comes down the pitch and he checks his shot and defends back to the bowler
pushed in on middle and leg and he clips it to square leg
flighted on middle and leg and he clips it to the on side
yet another indrifter, he shuffles and works it on its way to the on side
uses his feet and pushes it through the line to long-off
gets his leg forward and the ball lobs off his pads to the on side
drifts it in and then gets it to turn away, Watson watches the spin and defends
drops it fractionally short and he rocks back and cuts to sweeper cover
drops it quite short and he seizes on it early and pulls past mid-on, Misbah was fielding in that position and he didn't see it at all
gets across and works it with the turn to fine leg
flighted on middle and leg and he defends
slow through the air and he pushes it with the turn to long-on
slow through the air, he waits for it before softly pushing it towards mid-off
drops it fractionally short and Watson goes for a cross-batted swipe and gets a thick inside edge
much better, he gets right behind the line and pushes it back to the bowler
short and wide outside off, he slams it square of the wicket on the off side
keeps it nice and straight and Clarke defends off the full face of the bat
similar line and length, a restrictive line, another defensive shot back to the bowler
punches it straight to cover and tells his partner to wait
pushes it towards midwicket, the fielder ought to have saved that
full and pushed down the ground to long-off
clipped to short fine leg and they jog the single
chips down the pitch and pushes it straight back to the bowler
down the leg side and nudged wide of square leg
gets across his stumps and decides to defend with a dead bat back to the bowler
stands tall and punches it straight towards mid-off

Excellent delivery! That's a fast reverse swinging yorker which jams his toe in line with the leg stump, the ball rolls to the off side and Bowden has given it as runs, there was no bat involved I'm afraid that should have been given out, at least according to Hawkeye
defended on the front foot to the on side
comes down the track and pushes it to long-on
defended off the backfoot to cover for a single
pushes a low full toss straight to long-on for a single
tries to nudge it to the on side but the ball rolls off the pads
angles it across the right hander and he clips it to the on side
very very sloppy! Misbah picks it up at midwicket and blindly flicks it to the bowler's end, the only problem was that he missed the bowler and the stumps by about 5 miles
pushed wide of midwicket
gets forward and defends back to the bowler

Gul finally gets a reward, he lands it on a good length on the corridor outside the offstump and Clarke gets a very thin leading edge as he shapes to clip it to the on side, Gul beat the bat on a few occasions in his first spell so it was a matter of time before he claimed a wicket
gets reverse swing and Symonds pushes it back to the bowler
full and swinging in again and he pushes it to mid-on
angles it on the pads and he works it away behind square on the on side
shapes to punch but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads
keeps it just outside off and Symonds opts to shoulder arms, he watches it move inwards before reaching the keeper
gets it to turn in and he defends
this one skids through and turns and Watson just manages to get some bat on it, the edge rolls to gully
full on middle and off and he clips it to mid-on
gets across and pushes it to the off side
gets forward and pushes it to the bowler's leg
punches it to long-on and jogs the single
starts off his new spell with a short delivery and the batsman stands tall and fends it off
gets across and pushes it down the pitch
angles it into the right hander and he clips it behind square on the on side
rocks on the backfoot and pulls it to deep backward square-leg
full outside off and pushes it straight to extra cover
the slower one this time and Symonds checks his shot as he comes forward, cover picks it up
full outside off and he comes down the pitch and pushes it to long-on
shuffles it and glances to fine leg, Arafat was a little lazy in the chase but somehow managed to pull it back just inches before the rope
sharp turn and he defends back to the bowler
works it across the line and places it to deep midwicket
clips it straight to Misbah at midwicket
punched off the backfoot
punches it to the left of mid-off and Watson was a little slow off the blocks, luckily the throw is wide
plays it to the on side
gets on the front foot and punches it to sweeper cover
drops it short and he shuffles and tucks it to deep square leg
defended off the backfoot
tries to paddle it past the keeper but it was too wide
punched wide of the diving extra cover fielder
the doosra, he picks it early, rocks back and cuts to the off side
shuffles and nudges it to square leg, Symonds has to scamper back to his crease and the throw to Malik is quick and wide, he hurts his finger as he tries to gather the ball
stays back and taps it to the off side
shuffles and clips it with the turn to fine leg
he gets to the pitch and punches it hard to mid-off
makes room and cuts hard and finds Shehzad at point
gets right behind the line to a quick delivery and defends
fires in a quick googly and Watson can only defend it
after four scoreless deliveries he pulls hard with intent but mistimes it to long-on
he tosses it up and Symonds accepts the invite by getting forward and lofting well wide of mid-off's right, welcome boundary
kneels down for a premeditated sweep and he places it to deep square leg
checks his shot and the leading edge lobs towards short cover
tossed up outside off, it's a conventional offspinner and Symonds is a little lazy on the cut and he ends up chopping it onto the base of the offstump
flighted on middle and leg and he clips it to the on side
full on the pads and pushed towards mid-on
flighted on middle and leg, he gets on his knee and sweeps just wide of fine leg
full outside off and pushed towards mid-off
drops it short and he gets away with it as Watson makes room and slaps it straight to cover
flighted on middle and leg, he clips it to the on side

Afridi and Akmal are very confident they've git him and but the decision goes upstairs, Ferguson gets a thick inside edge onto his boot and the ball lobs to Akmal, they appeal for the catch, replays weren't exactly clear and he gets the benefit of the doubt
stays back and cuts to cover
pushes it back to the bowler
stays back and cuts to the off side
bowls it quicker and the ball straightens, too short as Ferguson rocks back and slaps it in the huge gap between point and cover
loses his line and strays wide down the leg side
stays back and punches it straight to mid-on
gets across and pushes it towards the covers
comes back in and he rocks back and cuts to short third  man
waits for the turn and punches it towards mid-on
lands outside off and he dabs it away late to third man
full and driven straight back to the bowler
gets away with a short ball as he pulls and finds the fielder at deep midwicket
flighted on middle and leg and he kneels down and sweeps behind square
forces it to fine leg and the the fielder sprints across and just manages to pull it back
drops it short and he pulls hard but mistimes it to deep square leg
shuffles and clips it to square leg
driven to the on side
plays top early and the ball skids through and clips his pads
waits for it to turn and defends
gets sharp turn from the rough and Ferguson defends it behind his front pad
walks across his stumps early and punches it with the turn to long-on
drops it a fraction too short and he gets his bottom hand working as he pulls it and finds the boundary at deep midwicket
strays too wide down the leg side, poor delivery
rocks back and punches it straight to cover
stays on the backfoot, moves his foot across and whips it back to the bowler
comes back in and he moves across and tucks it to the on side
short of a length on middle and leg, he pulls it down to deep midwicket
drops it towards short leg and Ferguson was quickly off the blocks
strays down the leg side
clipped to the on side
tries to work it away to the on side but the ball turns back in and clips his pad
turns in and the ball rolls off his pads to the off side
he attempts the reverse sweep but misses

Run-out chance! Ferguson clips it towards square leg and he turns quickly for the second run, Clarke sends him back and he's halfway down the pitch, the fielder fires the throw to the bowler who gets a bad bounce and fluffs it, otherwise Ferguson was in deep trouble
lovely shot! He drops it short and he halfway down on one knee and times the pull really well, the ball just drops short of the rope at deep square leg
full outside off and squirted to mid-off
another neat yorker and he jams it back to the bowler
whips it wide of midwicket and Shoaib runs across and cuts it off
inswinging yorker and he squirts it to long-off on the full
another excellent yorker and he squeezes it out in front of mid-off and sets off
the ball spins and stops on him as he tries to push it to the offside
stays back and punches it to midon
turns away sharply and he meets thin air as he shapes to cut
pushed to extra cover
dabbed to third man
steps down the track, comes to the pitch of the ball and he drives it firmly past extra cover and mid-off, nice shot
Ferguson taps it to the off side and hesitates initially but goes through with the run
drives firmly down the pitch and beats the bowler
angles it on the pads and he clips it to the on side
shuffles and works it wide of square leg, he's on 99
that ought to have been stopped, Ferguson moves a long way across his stumps and glances him towards short fine leg who doesn't really give his 100% on the dive
That's his 100! Shuffles and nudges to square leg, it's his second in ODIs, he's played with lots of concentration against the spinners
really wide down the leg side
full on the middle stump and he plays the reverse sweep to point
back of a length and tucked behind square on the on side
gets on his knee and tucks it to deep square leg, they think of a second run
clips it to the vacant spaces at deep square-leg and they put a lot of pressure on the fielder
too wide outside off and he gets away with it as Ferguson reaches out and chops it down to point
the slower ball and he shuffles across and tucks it to fine leg
full and straight and heaved down to long-on, a better throw from Gul would have had Watson on deep trouble
full on the offstump and powered down the ground to long-off
makes room to squeeze out a yorker and the ball lobs off the pitch and drops towards short leg
squirts out a yorker to Younis at short cover and they complete a sharp single
goes for a huge slog and Ajmal cleverly drops the doosra and beats him
punched to the right of long-on
he attempts a reverse sweep and nearly loses his footing as he tries to keep his backfoot rooted to the crease, Akmal whips off the bails and the third umpire takes a look, he was safe
chips down the track and checks his shot
drifts down the leg side and he sweeps to fine leg
steps down the track and he punches him down to the covers
strays too wide outside off, Watson tries in vain to get some bat on ball
147 kph, searing yorker outside off and he fails to dig it out

inswinging yorker on middle and leg and he forces it hard down to long-on, Misbah fires a flat throw to the bowler who whips off the bails, the third umpire takes a look, I think Ferguson is quite lucky to be there because it looked as if his bat was on the line
Dropped Watson bends down for a wild slog and mishits it to Gul at midwicket, he fails to get under the ball as he pedals backwards
he drills it to long-on and they take another chance with Misbah at long-on, the throw is wayward
makes room and squeezes it to the off side
gets forward and drives just wide of long-off, it's another wayward throw and Australia get to 250

inn2.comm: has him driving away from the body straightaway, the ball goes straight through and beats the edge
strays down the leg side and wide called, Haddin does well to cover the movement
half volley outside off and driven to cover point

terrible start for Pakistan! Tucks the ball to the on side and Laughlin runs across to his right, slides and takes aim at the non-striker's end while still on all fours, Butt turns around, it's a direct hit and Butt was nowhere in the scene, it's a no ball as well
Free Hit Swings wildly off one arm and nearly chops the stumps behind him, the ball clips his body and rolls away
keeps it on a length outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching the keeper
gets right behind the line and pushes it to mid-on
drives it to mid-off
swings away and lands on a full length and he drives to mid-off
full again and he defends on the front foot
gets across and pushes it to the on side
close call for Younis as he gets a thick leading edge which drops short of short cover
drops it short and he stands on one leg and pulls to square leg
stands tall and punches it to the off side
good length on the offstump and he gets right behind the line and defends
lands it outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching the keeper
digs one in short and the ball flies over Shehzad

that's a brute of a delivery! Shehzad tries to fend off a quick bouncer and the ball lobs off the top of the bat and Haddin takes the catch, Shehzad walks and Bowden consults with the other umpire and reverses the decision on the grounds that it was above the shoulder, but I'm afraid it was a legitimate delivery and Shehzad is very lucky
full outside off and driven to third man
lands outside off and he leaves it alone
short and wide and he reaches out and cuts wide of backward point, third man is square
he drives with the swing to cover
prods forward, hangs his bat out and the away swing beats him
slower ball, he gets forward and taps it to cover and takes a quick single
drives hard down the pitch and the bowler does well to slide and cut it off
hangs his bat out and gets a thick inside edge onto his pads, his feet are not moving tonight
angles it on the body and the ball clips his body and rolls to the on side
gets across and taps it back to the bowler
drives a full delivery down the practice pitch and finds mid-off
this one cuts away off the pitch and nearly shaves the outside edge as he tries to punch him without moving his feet
angles away from the right hander and he's beaten yet again
gets across his stumps and defends to the on side
drives uppishly away from the body and beats a diving Hopes at backward point
hesitation! He punches one to the covers and sets off, turns around and the throw is just wide at the striker's end
gets forward and drives inside out wide of cover
lands on the offstump and he gets behind the line and defends
stays back and he punches it off the full face of the bat to midwicket
138 kph, lands it outside off and he gets beside the line and defends
turns the bat and times it well towards mid-on and the fielder does really well to get to his right and effect a sliding save
close to a run out! Bollinger dives to his left and deflects the ball towards the stumps and had the ball hit the stumps Shehzad would have gone, it missed the stumps by  a whisker
lovely shot, overpitched on middle and off and Younis drives off the full face of the bat and beats the bowler
gets forward and the ball edges onto his body and rolls away
bangs it in short and Younis gets on top of the bounce and he pulls over midwicket, all power behind that shot
gets beside the line and steers it wide of backward point
stays back at the crease and punches it towards mid-on
fractionally short and he pulls but doesn't get his placement spot on and Hopes does well to slide to his left and stop a few runs
angles it down to third man, he plays it with the swing
full and swinging away, he pushes forward and finds mid-off
bang on target - on the offstump and he steers it to the off side
stays at the crease and punches it on the up and beats the narrow gap between the covers
taps it to the off side, tells his captain to stay put
gets a thick edge which just beats first slip, Hilfy does well at third man to slide and save a boundary
gets a thick edge onto his body which rolls to the on side
gets his bat right in front of the offstump and steers it to the off side
reaches out to an away swinger and drives very uppishly past the vacant gully region
swivels a little too early on the pull and he mistimes it to deep square leg
gives him width and he slaps it hard on the front foot and finds cover
drives hard on the front foot but he cannot beat mid-off
gets right behind the line and defends down the track
slaps it hard on the offside but the ball flashes to Watson at short point on the first bounce
short ball and he pulls it behind square on the on side
punches it in front of mid-on and puts pressure on the fielder by setting off for a single, the fielder fumbles
driven hard and he can't beat the infied on the off side, Australia are plugging the gaps
mistimes the drive on the front foot and he finds Symonds at short extra cover
punches it on the front foot just wide of mid-off and he calls for the run quickly
the slower ball and he gets well forward and defends
flighted outside off, he pushes it to midwicket
flighted on middle and off, he chips it in the air to mid-on
defends with a dead bat to the on side and sets off for a quick single
gives him a fraction of width and he chops it towards point
angled on the pads and he clips it towards short fine leg
angled it across the right hander and he nudges it to the on side
he plays an elegant backfoot punch in the gap between midwicket and square leg and Ferguson gives the chase, pulls the ball back but the ball rolls back to the ropes
angles it to third man
gets on the front foot and drives through the off side
loses his concentration and drives away from the body without getting to the pitch of the ball
takes the aerial route by chipping it over mid-on but he knows where the fielders are, the ball drops in front of long-on
shuffles across and he fails to get bat on ball for a yorker, the ball clips his pads and rolls away, the bowler appeals but the ball was missing leg
clips it with the turn to deep midwicket

he takes a couple of paces down the pitch and tries to go downtown with the turn, he doesn't go through with the shot and hence fails to get the elevation, Hilfenhaus runs to his right and takes the catch at wide long-on
gets right behind the line and defends
gets across his stumps, waits for the turn and defends soflty
nearly gives a bat-pad catch to Ferguson at forward short-leg
close! He defends with soft hands and the ball nearly rolls to the stumps
starts off his new spell with a wide down the leg side
full on the legstump and tapped to the on side
gets across and taps it very softly to midwicket
overpitched outside off and Shehzad gets on his knee and plays an elegant square drive past the gap between cover and point
defends on the backfoot towards cover and he sets off
stays on the backfoot and steers it towards gully
angles away from the right hander and the ball beats the outside edge
lunges forward and there's turn and bounce, no bat involved luckily
lobs off the pads and drops just wide of forward short-leg
gets to the pitch and drives just wide if mid-off and sets off
clips it with the turn wide of midwicket
nudges it to fine leg and Bolinger fires a powerful throw while still on his knees

Hauritz really deserved it! The ball turns very sharply off the rough and Shehzad shapes to cut but the turn foxes him, the ball clips the top flap of his pad bang in front of the stumps, Aleem Dar is convinced, easy decision
angles it on the pads and he clips it to deep square leg

shot of the evening, Kamran shows the full face of the bat and pushes a half volley right back past the bowler, the ball disappears quickly and Kamran is so proud of that shot that he walks down the pitch and continues to show the full face of the bat
the ball darts away sharply off the pitch and foxes everybody, Haddin does well to fall to his right and save it
shows the full face of the bat and defends
opens the face of the bat and steers it wide of second slip
